{#def mngr_forward_origin, trigger_x=0, trigger_y=0, trigger_w=0, trigger_h=38, offset_x=-24, offset_y=2 #}
{#
  Standalone sidebar page loaded into the shared modal WebContentsView
  when the user opens the sidebar. The modal view covers the full window
  content area, the body is the transparent backdrop, and the floating
  panel is pinned at a position derived from the caller's trigger
  geometry. This template is a pure POSITIONING SHELL: the menu interior
  (grouped workspace rows + "New workspace") is the mithril WorkspaceMenu
  component, mounted by the inline script below. Clicks on the backdrop
  (anywhere outside the panel) dismiss the modal via the component's
  overlay-modal wiring (host.closeModal()); the Escape key is handled by
  main.js's modal before-input-event listener (see openModal in
  electron/main.js), so this page does not install its own Escape
  handler. The panel's height comes from its own flex content -- no JS
  measurement or Electron-side bounds math is needed.

  Position model: the trigger (the chrome page's #workspace-switcher-btn
  in the titlebar breadcrumb) passes its viewport-relative rect (trigger_x,
  trigger_y, trigger_w, trigger_h) plus a caller-chosen offset (offset_x,
  offset_y). The menu anchors its top-left at the trigger's bottom-left + offset:
    left = trigger_x + offset_x
    top  = trigger_y + trigger_h + offset_y
  Because the chrome view and the modal view share the same window
  coordinate space, the trigger's rect translates directly. The panel
  carries a uniform 4px pad on all sides (``p-1``) with 2px between
  entries (``gap-0.5``); each row adds its own ``px-2`` for the hover
  highlight's inset. The default offset_x (-24) lines a row's workspace-name
  label up under the breadcrumb's workspace-name text: the label sits 30px
  inside the menu's left edge (p-1 4 + px-2 8 + dot 10 + gap-2 8) while the
  breadcrumb name sits 6px inside the trigger, so the menu shifts left by 24.

  Defaults (no query params): anchor a 38px-tall element at the top-left
  of the window, nudged 24px left and 2px below it. That's the right shape
  for the titlebar's first button without any caller customization.

  mngr_forward_origin is exposed via data-mngr-forward-origin so the menu
  can build the cross-origin /goto/<agent>/ URL the plugin serves.
  backup_health.js supplies the shared backup-warning cache the row badges
  read through the store bridge.
#}
{% set _body_attrs %}data-mngr-forward-origin="{{ mngr_forward_origin }}"{% endset %}
{% set _scripts %}
<script src="/_static/backup_health.js"></script>
<script>
  window.MindsUI.mountWorkspaceMenu(document.getElementById('sidebar-menu'), { isOverlayModal: true });
</script>
{% endset %}
{% set _menu_left = trigger_x + offset_x %}
{% set _menu_top = trigger_y + trigger_h + offset_y %}
<OverlaySurface title="Switch workspace"
                body_attrs={{ _body_attrs }}
                scripts={{ _scripts }}>
  <div id="sidebar-backdrop" class="fixed inset-0">
    <div id="sidebar-menu"
         style="left:{{ _menu_left }}px; top:{{ _menu_top }}px;"
         class="dark absolute w-[280px] flex flex-col gap-0.5 p-1 rounded-lg border border-subtle bg-surface-primary shadow-overlay overflow-hidden"></div>
  </div>
</OverlaySurface>
